snippet.textDisplay: About this film, as a Chinese, I want to say, it is adapted to a certain extent, part of the plot, according to Disney animation part according to the famous epic plot "mulan", coupled with the adaptation of the content, if you are understanding the classical legend story hua mulan, you will find that the Disney animation added a lot of elements such as mushu funny elements, while the movie is more serious, after all, is a story about the war in ancient China. I can give you a general explanation about the addition of female characters to the villain. It is a translation problem. The woman belongs to the role of the shaman master and so on. In addition, xiongnu (xianbei tribe) in different places treated women differently, some of them did not discriminate against women, and some even respected women, but in the central plains, men were given priority.

snippet.textDisplay: Not getting the hype tbh. This trailer didn't make me cry or feel anything, like everyone else are saying. They speak badly pronounced English and have stupid "Chinese special effects" like running up walls and turning into an eagle, and no doubt other supposed "kungfu" stuff that defies physics. The acting seems deadpan too and without true emotion/hardship in training. I loved the cartoon movie and I'm a big supporter of women in mens' roles, but this trailer really doesn't look great.

snippet.textDisplay:
Hate to kill the vibe, but the lead actress (Liu Yifei) condones the police actions towards the Hong Kong protestors... Some say to "BOYCOTT this movie". I can't say I blame them.
I'm happy to get a movie that seems to give some solid respect to the source material. But I'm probably not going to see it, because I can't knowingly support someone who can't or won't understand the value in fighting for freedom and for your country (as the Hong Kong protesters are doing), even after playing a character who was doing exactly that... Big "yikes" there.
